# Acme Learning Chat Platform — Setup Instructions

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js 20+**
- **PostgreSQL 15+** (running locally)
- **Redis 7+** (optional — the app gracefully falls back if unavailable)

---

## Project Structure

```
CMS/
├── backend/
│   ├── prisma/
│   │   ├── schema.prisma      ← 12 tables, all enums, full relations
│   │   └── seed.ts            ← 1 org, 6 users, 3 batches, memberships, 10 messages
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── controllers/       ← auth, batch, member, message, modqueue, notification,
│   │   │                        subscription, admin, mentor, profile
│   │   ├── routes/index.ts    ← all REST endpoints prefixed /api
│   │   ├── services/          ← auth, batch, member, message, modqueue, notification,
│   │   │                        subscription, admin
│   │   ├── middlewares/       ← auth (JWT), errorHandler, rateLimiter, upload (multer)
│   │   ├── sockets/index.ts   ← Socket.IO events with auth middleware
│   │   ├── utils/             ← prisma client, redis client, jwt, errors, permissions
│   │   ├── validators/        ← all Zod schemas
│   │   └── index.ts           ← Express + Socket.IO entry point
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── package.json
│   └── tsconfig.json
└── frontend/
    ├── src/
    │   ├── pages/             ← Login, Register, Dashboard, BatchChat, Admin, Mentor,
    │   │                        Subscription, Profile
    │   ├── store/             ← authStore, batchStore, messageStore, notificationStore, uiStore
    │   ├── hooks/useSocket.ts ← Socket.IO hook with all event handlers
    │   ├── api/client.ts      ← Axios instance with auto-refresh interceptor
    │   ├── App.tsx            ← Routes with ProtectedRoute and RoleRoute wrappers
    │   └── main.tsx           ← React entry with QueryClient + BrowserRouter
    ├── .env.example
    ├── index.html
    ├── tailwind.config.js
    ├── postcss.config.js
    ├── vite.config.ts
    └── package.json
```

---

## Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend
cp .env.example .env         # Edit DATABASE_URL to match your PostgreSQL
npm install
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
npx prisma db seed
npm run dev                  # tsx watch → http://localhost:4000
```

## Frontend Setup

```bash
cd frontend
cp .env.example .env
npm install
npm run dev                  # Vite → http://localhost:5173
```

